I was on the second question and didn't get much time to find the solution for it. Interrupted by interruptions by lots of chatgpt, my group eventually had to end. My only solution for this question involves the binomial formula, and differencing right side with respect to $x$ and substituting $x=0$ and then cancelling $\dfrac{1}{15}$ from both sides, like so:
\begin{align}
&\left.\frac{d^n}{dx^n}\left(\frac{1}{5-17x}\right)\right|_{x=0}=\omega n\left(\frac{1}{15}\right)^{n-1}
\to \frac{17^n}{5^{n+1}}=\omega n\left(\frac{1}{15}\right)^{n-1}\\
\to &\omega=5^2\cdot \frac{3^{n-1}\cdot 17^{n+1}}{5^{2n-2}}=\left\{n=1\right\}\to \omega=4605
\end{align}
